3A%2F%2Fc.ndtvimg.com%2F2024-12%2Fnkfn1s78_syrian-celebrations_625x300_10_December_24.jpg%3Fim%3DFaceCrop%2Calgorithm%3Ddnn%2Cwidth%3D1200%2Cheight%3D738%5C%22%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20regime%20change%20in%20Syria%20came%20as%20a%20rebirth%20for%20the%20thousands%20of%20inmates%20in%20Syria's%20prisons%20and%20detention%20centres%2C%20many%20of%20them%20jailed%20for%20dissent.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAccording%20to%20news%20agency%20AFP%2C%20thousands%20gathered%20outside%20Saydnaya%20prison%20near%20Damascus%2C%20synonymous%20with%20the%20worst%20atrocities%20of%20Assad's%20rule%2C%20to%20look%20for%20their%20relatives.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EOver%201%20lakh%20inmates%20are%20believed%20to%20have%20died%20--%20including%20executions%20and%20natural%20deaths%20--%20in%20Syrian%20prisons%20during%20the%20Assad%20rule%2C%20according%20to%20a%202021%20report%20by%20the%20UK-based%20Syrian%20Observatory%20for%20Human%20Rights.%20Of%20them%2C%20more%20than%2030%2C000%20died%20in%20Saydnaya%20alone.%20An%20Amnesty%20International%20investigation%20found%20that%20%26quot%3Bmurder%2C%20torture%2C%20enforced%20disappearances%20and%20extermination%20carried%20out%20at%20Saydnaya%20since%202011%20have%20been%20perpetrated%20as%20part%20of%20an%20attack%20against%20the%20civilian%20population%20that%20has%20been%20widespread%2C%20as%20well%20as%20systematic%2C%20and%20carried%20out%20in%20furtherance%20of%20state%20policy%26quot%3B.%20Such%20were%20the%20tales%20of%20torture%20in%20Saydnaya%20that%20it%20was%20known%20as%20a%20%26quot%3Bhuman%20slaughterhouse%26quot%3B.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWith%20Assad%20gone%2C%20the%20family%20members%20of%20these%20inmates%2C%20many%20of%20whom%20have%20been%20detained%20for%20years%2C%20are%20looking%20for%20them.%20Among%20them%20is%20Aida%20Taha%2C%2065%2C%20who%20is%20looking%20for%20her%20brother%2C%20arrested%20in%202012.%20%26quot%3BI%20ran%20like%20crazy.%20But%20I%20found%20out%20that%20some%20prisoners%20were%20still%20in%20the%20basements.%20There%20are%20three%20or%20four%20floors%20underground%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20told%20AFP.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EMany%20of%20the%20prisoners%20who%20have%20managed%20to%20escape%20from%20the%20now-unmanned%20prisons%20roam%20the%20streets%20of%20Damascus%2C%20with%20unmistakable%20signs%20of%20torture%20and%20hunger.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EA%20civil%20servant%20at%20the%20finance%20ministry%20said%20people%20were%20scared%20to%20speak%20out.%20%26quot%3BIt's%20indescribable.%20We%20never%20thought%20this%20nightmare%20would%20end.%20We%20are%20reborn.%20We%20were%20afraid%20to%20speak%20for%2055%20years%2C%20even%20at%20home.%20We%20used%20to%20say%20the%20walls%20had%20ears%2C%26quot%3B%20Rim%20Ramadan%2C%2049%2C%20told%20AFP.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ESyria's%20parliament%2C%20earlier%20pro-Assad%2C%20has%20said%20it%20supports%20%26quot%3Bthe%20will%20of%20the%20people%20to%20build%20a%20new%20Syria%20towards%20a%20better%20future%20governed%20by%20law%20and%20justice%26quot%3B.%20Baath%20party%20has%20said%20it%20will%20support%20%26quot%3Ba%20transitional%20phase%20in%20Syria%20aimed%20at%20defending%20the%20unity%20of%20the%20country.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHayat%20Tahrir%20al-Sham%2C%20which%20led%20the%20rebel%20groups'%20blitzkrieg%2C%20was%20earlier%20banned%20by%20Western%20powers%20for%20its%20links%20with%20Al-Qaeda.%20Over%20the%20years%2C%20the%20organisation%20has%20tried%20to%20soften%20its%20image.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAs%20Syria%20looks%20to%20rebuild%2C%20Germany%20and%20France%20have%20said%20they%20were%20ready%20to%20cooperate%20with%20the%20new%20leadership%20%26quot%3Bon%20the%20basis%20of%20fundamental%20human%20rights%20and%20the%20protection%20of%20ethnic%20and%20religious%20minorities%26quot%3B.%20British%20Prime%20Minister%20Keir%20Starmer%20has%20said%20HTS%20must%20reject%20%26quot%3Bterrorism%20and%20violence%26quot%3B%20before%20Britain%20can%20engage%20with%20it.%20US%20State%20Secretary%20Antony%20Blinken%20Wash