r%20parents%20age%2C%20become%20more%20frail%2C%20and%20then%20die.%20Nancy%20never%20chose%20that%20for%20herself.%20I%20was%20maybe%20catastrophizing%2C%20but%20the%20guilt%20ate%20me%20up.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EAnd%20so%20along%20came%20Edith%2C%20who's%20now%204%20months%20old.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22d413cd5e-3ca6-4308-b100-32d06754903b%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3EPeople%20didn't%20understand%20why%20I%20wanted%20a%203rd%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EIt%20was%20a%20traumatic%20journey%20to%20have%20Edith.%20At%20first%2C%20some%20friends%20didn't%20understand%20why%20I'd%20have%20a%20third%20when%20I%20already%20found%20it%20tough%20having%20two%20kids%20and%20a%20full%20time%20banking%20job.%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EI%20was%20determined%2C%20though.%20I%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fafter-two-miscarriages-doubt-if-i-wanted-a-baby-2021-7%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3Ehad%20three%20miscarriages%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E%20before%20having%20Edith.%20Physically%20and%20mentally%2C%20my%20body's%20really%20been%20through%20it%2C%20so%20I%20haven't%20come%20out%20of%20this%20pregnancy%20in%20great%20mental%20health.%20I%20don't%20feel%20seven%20years%20older%20than%20when%20I%20first%20became%20a%20mom%3B%20I%20feel%2020%20years%20older.%20It'll%20get%20better%3B%20I'm%20just%20trying%20to%20get%20used%20to%20life%20as%20a%20family%20of%20five.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20upside%20is%20that%20the%20crushing%20guilt%20I%20felt%20lifted%20the%20minute%20Edith%20arrived%2C%20and%20I%20relaxed%20a%20bit.%20Of%20course%2C%20Edith%20may%20also%20want%20to%20be%20her%20own%20person.%20But%20now%20the%20responsibility%20of%20care%20for%20Mabel%20is%20shared%20after%20I'm%20no%20longer%20here%20or%20able.%20Some%20of%20the%20grief%20about%20giving%20birth%20to%20a%20disabled%20child%20%E2%80%94%20which%20is%20taboo%20to%20discuss%