0%94%20given%20name%20Shawn%20Carter%20%E2%80%94%20complained%20that%20the%20accuser%20should%20not%20be%20allowed%20to%20tarnish%20his%20name%20while%20hiding%20her%20identity.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20a%2029-page%20filing%20in%20federal%20court%20in%20Manhattan%2C%20Carter%20says%20that%20the%20woman%20had%20previously%20sought%20money%20from%20him%20and%20that%20he%20had%20refused%20to%20pay.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20filing%20is%20Carter's%20first%20formal%20response%20to%20the%20new%20accusations%2C%20and%20follows%20his%20strongly-worded%20denial%20from%20Sunday%20on%20his%20company%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22%20nofollow%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fx.com%2FRocNation%2Fstatus%2F1865917852542247358%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3ERoc%20Nation's%20X%20%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3Eaccount.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ECarter's%20attorney%2C%20Alex%20Spiro%2C%20said%20in%20Monday's%20filing%20that%20the%20lawsuit%20is%20a%20good%20thing.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BNow%2C%20at%20last%2C%20the%20false%2C%20unfounded%20allegations%20that%20underlie%20this%20campaign%20of%20extortion%20are%20having%20judicial%20light%20shined%20on%20them%2C%26quot%3B%20Spiro%20wrote.%20%26quot%3BExcept%20that%20this%20Plaintiff%20is%20bringing%20them%20as%20a%20Doe%2C%20who%20would%20continue%20to%20hide%20under%20cover%20of%20darkness.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhen%20the%20Jane%20Doe%20first%20filed%20her%20lawsuit%2C%20in%20October%2C%20she%20had%20named%20only%20Combs%2C%20his%20companies%20and%20his%20associates%20as%20defendants.%20On%20Sunday%20she%20filed%20an%20updated%20lawsuit%20that%20removed%20a%20reference%20to%20%26quot%3BCelebrity%20A%26quot%3B%20and%20added%20%26quot%3BShawn%20Carter%26quot%3B%20as%20defendant.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BAnother%20celebrity%20stood%20by%20and%20watched%20as%20Combs%20and%20Carter%20took%20turns%20assaulting%20the%20minor%2C%26quot%3B%20the%20updated%20lawsuit%20reads%2C%20continuing%20to%20protect%20the%20identity%20of%20that%20third%20person.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20woman's%20lawyer%2C%20Tony%20Buzbee%2C%20confirmed%20to%20Business%20Insider%20on%20Sunday%20there%20had%20been%20previous%20contact%20between%20the%20Jane%20Doe%20and%20Carter.%20Buzbee%20said%20he%20had%20sent%20a%20letter%20to%20Carter%20requesting%20mediation%20before%20naming%20him%20in%20Sunday's%20updated%20lawsuit.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ECarter%20responded%20to%20that%20outreach%20with%20a%20campaign%20of%20%26quot%3Bharassment%2C%20bullying%2C%20and%20intimidation%20against%20Plaintiff's%20lawyers%2C%20their%20families%2C%20employees%2C%20and%20former%20associates%20in%20an%20attempt%20to%20silence%20Plaintiff%20from%20naming%20Jay-Z%20herein%2C%26quot%3B%20the%20updated%20lawsuit%20alleges.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20fighting%20to%20keep%20his%20client's%20Jane%20Doe%20status%20as%20the%20lawsuit%20proceeds%2C%20Buzbee%20told%20a%20federal%20judge%20on%20Sunday%20that%20anonymity%20is%20necessary%20to%20protect%20all%20of%20his%20clients%20who%20are%20accusing%20Combs%20of%20sexual%20assault.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BMy%20firm%20currently%20represents%20over%20200%20clients%20with%20claims%20against%20Mr.%20Combs%2C%26quot%3B%20Buzbee%20wrote%20in%20a%20filing%20on%20Sunday.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMore%20than%2080%20percent%20of%20these%20clients%20have%20said%20Combs%20threatened%20them%20or%20their%20family%20members%20in%20hopes%20of%20keeping%20them%20quiet%2C%20Buzbee%20wrote.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BFor%20many%20of%20the%20clients%20referenced%20above%2C%20Mr.%20Combs'%20threats%20of%20violence%20were%20a%20primary%20reason%20why%20they%20did%20not%20speak%20out%20or%20file%20lawsuits%20earlier.%20Most%20of%20our%20clients%20still%20fear%20retribution%20and%20have%20conditioned%20moving%20forward%20on%20anonymity%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20wrote.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESince%20mid-October%2C%20Buzbee%20has%20filed%20some%2020%20lawsuits%20in%20which%20men%20and%20women%20allege%20they%20were%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fcategory%2Fdidd